  "prompt": "What is the purpose of json?",
  "response": "JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) serves several important purposes in data exchange and storage:\n\n1. Data Interchange Format\n- Lightweight and easy-to-read text format for transmitting data\n- Language-independent data format\n- Commonly used for sending data between web servers and web applications\n\n2. Data Storage\n- Stores structured data in a human-readable format\n- Supports nested data structures\n- Can represent complex data types like objects and arrays\n\n3. Key Benefits\n- Lightweight and compact compared to XML\n- Easy for humans to read and write\n- Easy for machines to parse and generate\n- Language-independent (supported by most programming languages)\n\n4. Common Use Cases\n- API responses\n- Configuration files\n- Data serialization\n- Storing settings and preferences\n- Web service communication\n\n5. Data Structure Support\n- Key-value pairs\n- Arrays\n- Nested objects\n- Supports basic data types:\n  - Strings\n  - Numbers\n  - Booleans\n  - Null\n  - Objects\n  - Arrays\n\nExample JSON:\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n  \"age\": 30,\n  \"isStudent\": false,\n  \"hobbies\": [\"reading\", \"coding\", \"hiking\"]\n}\n```\n\nJSON provides a versatile and efficient way to represent and exchange structured data.",
